# Claude Guidelines

When contributing to NourishOS:

- Think in systems, not isolated features.
- Follow the existing architecture and module boundaries.
- Reuse shared services instead of duplicating functionality.
- Maintain consistency with the PRD, Architecture, RBAC, Firestore Schema, and Feature Specifications.
- Favor modular, maintainable, and production-ready solutions.
- When proposing new functionality, explain its impact on Firestore, Cloud Functions, RBAC, Audit Logs, Notifications, and Reporting.
- Keep the user experience simple for outlet staff while providing comprehensive capabilities for management.

> **Principle:** Every feature should strengthen the vision of NourishOS as a unified, enterprise-grade operating system for multi-outlet F&B businesses.

